OL,3,GLondon & South East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FBright spells and frequent
OL,6,Fshowers through the day, some of which
OL,7,Fare likely to be heavy and thundery.
OL,8,FWinds are light becoming breezy along
OL,9,Fthe coast.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FTurning increasingly cloudy
OL,12,Ffrom the west as a band of rain moves
OL,13,Feastwards overnight across all areas
OL,14,Fby the morning. Feeling cool in the
OL,15,Fwind.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FCloudy and breezy, with rain
OL,18,Fclearing to the east during the
OL,19,Fmorning. Followed by frequent heavy
OL,20,Fshowers in the afternoon before easing
OL,21,Finto the evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
